  Filmmaking Terms Resources

Below are a few filmmaking resources that you can use to get acquainted with various filmmaking terms and concepts.

Filmmaking Terms PDF - This PDF has virtually every filmmaking term you can imagine. It's not pretty, but it is dang helpful for understanding the concepts.

Filmmaking Websites:

  1. Filmmaker Magazine is a great resource for filmmakers of all levels. It covers a wide range of topics, including filmmaking techniques, film history, and interviews with filmmakers.
  2. No Film School is another great resource for filmmakers. It offers articles, tutorials, and interviews on a variety of filmmaking topics.
  3. IndieWire is a website that covers the independent film industry. It offers news, reviews, and interviews about independent films.
  4. Studio Binder is a company that creates software for filmmakers, but they also have one of the best blogs for learning filmmaking techniques.
  5. PremiumBeat is a royalty-free music website that actually has one of the best collections of filmmaking articles on the planet. I also used to help run this site so I'm a little biased. They don't update the site as often, but there are plenty oldie-but-goodies in there.
